parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if the vehicle is unable to stop or loses control.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates rapidly without warning
even when the driver's foot is not on the gas pedal
and may occur in slow-speed situations like drive-thru lanes or traffic.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling or loss of power can cause accidents, especially if the vehicle is traveling at high speeds or in heavy traffic, and can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The engine shuts off or loses power while driving
often accompanied by warning lights or messages
and may occur without warning or symptoms.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel pump issues can cause engine stalling or loss of power, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience fuel pump failure
resulting in engine stalling or loss of power
and may be accompanied by warning lights or messages.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transfer case failure can cause drivetrain failure, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if the vehicle is traveling at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience drivetrain failure
resulting in loud banging or grinding noises
and may be accompanied by warning lights or messages.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: AWD system failure can cause loss of traction or control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if the vehicle is traveling at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience AWD system failure
resulting in the illumination of warning lights
and may be accompanied by loss of power or traction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission issues can cause loss of power or control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if the vehicle is traveling at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience transmission issues
resulting in grinding or whining noises
and may be accompanied by loss of power or acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Sudden Engine Stalling and Shutting Off
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling and shutting off of the engine can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially fatal injuries, especially when occurring on highways or busy roads.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts off without warning
often while driving at moderate to high speeds
accompanied by beeping or warning messages; the vehicle may restart but shut down again; no warning lights may be illuminated; the vehicle may hesitate or buck before stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel System Issues (Possible Fuel Pump Failure)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel system issues can cause the engine to stall or shut off, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially fatal injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts off without warning

often while driving at moderate to high speeds; the vehicle may hesitate or buck before stalling; the fuel level may not be accurately displayed; the vehicle may shut off despite having sufficient fuel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The ergonomic design of the gas pedal can cause discomfort, pain, and muscle strain, potentially leading to loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: The gas pedal requires excessive force to be depressed
causing pain and muscle strain in the driver's leg; the issue may only be noticeable after prolonged driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The windshield may be prone to chipping or cracking, potentially obstructing the driver's view and causing accidents.
symptoms: Small stones or debris can easily chip or crack the front windshield
even at moderate speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power while driving, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power while driving
the vehicle sputters or struggles to accelerate
the RPMs surge or drop suddenly
the vehicle may enter limp mode
and there may be no warning lights or error codes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel system issues, including faulty fuel injectors, can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power while driving, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power while driving
the Check Engine light comes on
the vehicle struggles to accelerate
and there may be no warning lights or error codes.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Random Engine Stalling and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected loss of power and engine stalling can lead to accidents, especially when driving on highways, and can cause safety incidents in traffic, putting the driver and other road users at risk.
symptoms: The engine stalls or loses power while driving
the car comes to a complete stop
the engine jolts or lunges before stalling
the car will not accelerate
the power stays on but the engine stops
the battery and engine lights come on.
